{"lemma":"مُسْنَدٌ","slug":"مُسْنَدٌ","root":"س.ن.د","root_slug":"س-ن-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ن-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20933"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَسْنَدَ (ʔasnada).","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَسْنَدَ (ʔasnada).; backed-up, fortified, held-up (describes having an unverifiable chain of narrators for a Prophetic Hadith alleging its authenticity)","examples":[{"text":"أحاديث غير مُسْنَدَة","english":"Hadiths with no narrators mentioned"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"musnad (collection of Prophetic Hadiths with narrators)","examples":[{"text":"مُسْنَد الإمام أحمد","english":"The Musnad of Imam Ahmad ibn Hanbal"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"predicate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prop, rest, support"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of أَسْنَدَ (ʔasnada, “to support”).\n\nTool noun from the root س ن د (s n d)."},"ipa":["/mus.nad/","/mas.nad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20933","headword_ar":"مُسْنَدٌ","root":"snd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of 4,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made to lean, rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., against, or upon, a thing: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed, propped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  Hence used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misonadN","text_ar":"مِسْنَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as being a thing set up]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanadN","text_ar":"سَنَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)  A tradition ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traced up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attributed, to the author thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L, K, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rested on his authority by the mention of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 4,) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the mention, uninterruptedly, in ascending order, of the persons by whom it has been transmitted, up to the Prophet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L, KT;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the mention of him who has related it from the Prophet when only one has intervened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murosalN","text_ar":"مُرْسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoqiTiEN","text_ar":"مُنْقِطِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnqTE","text_ar":"منقطع"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interrupted in the mention of the persons by whom it has been transmitted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAnidu","text_ar":"مَسَانِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) agreeably with analogy, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAniydu","text_ar":"مَسَانِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Esh-Sháfi'ee, K,) which latter has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"added to render the sound of the kesreh more full; or, accord. to some, it is a dial. var.; and accord. to some, agreeable with analogy. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEiY~N","text_ar":"دَعِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning (assumed tropical:)  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who claims as his father a person who is not his father;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adopted son;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parentage, is suspected"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saniydN","text_ar":"سَنِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, L, K; [see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asar~u","text_ar":"اَسَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariymN","text_ar":"كَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadu","text_ar":"المُسْنَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Sb, signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the subject"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a proposition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"المُسْنَدُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the attribute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predicate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) of, accord. to Kh, a proposition consists of a ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanad","text_ar":"سَنَد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musonad A_ilayoh","text_ar":"مُسْنَد اـِلَيْه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu A@ll~`hi rajulN","text_ar":"عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [for ex.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ebd All~`h","text_ar":"عبد اللّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snd","text_ar":"سند"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjl SAlH","text_ar":"رجل صالح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"msnd Alyh","text_ar":"مسند اليه"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, L:) [but accord. to other authors, and general modern usage, and agreeably with the proper meanings of the terms,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadu","text_ar":"المُسْنَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning the attributed) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the attribute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predicate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"المُسْنَدُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (meaning that to which a thing or an accident is attributed) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the subject."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Himyeree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Himyeritic, character of writing; the character of Himyer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differing from the modern Arabic character:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) they used to write it commonly in the days of their rule; and AHát says that it continued in use among them in El-Yemen in his day [i. e. in the latter half of the second century of the Flight and the former half of the third century]: (M, TA:) Abu-l-'Abbás says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadu","text_ar":"المُسْنَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the language of the sons of Seth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA;) [i. e. the language written in the character so called;] and the like is said in the “ Sirr es-Siná'ah ” of IJ. (TA.) [See also De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., sec. ed., vol. ii., p. 122 of the Ar. text, and 311 of the transl.] ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time, from the beginning of the world to its end;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time absolutely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long unlimited time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time without end;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, M, A, K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu A=xira Almusonadi","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ ا=خِرَ المُسْنَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it to the end of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A=tiyhi yada","text_ar":"لَا ا=تِيهِ يَدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusonadi","text_ar":"المُسْنَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","L","K","TA","KT","M","O","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%86%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"مسند","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23641#c356e7","body_html":"<span>المسند من الحديث: خلاف المرسل، وهو الذي اتصل إسناده إلى رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم، وهو ثلاثة أقسام: المتواتر، والمشهور، والآحاد. والمسند قد يكون متصلًا ومنقطعًا، والمتصل مثل ما روى مالك عن نافع، عن ابن عمر، عن رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم والمنقطع مثل ما روى مالك، عن الزهري، عن ابن عباس، عن رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم، فهذا مسند؛ لأنه قد أسند إلى رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم، ومنقطع؛ لأن الزهري لم يسمع من ابن عباس، رضي الله عنه.</span>"}]}}